data.chText: 审查；调查；考查；考察
data.enText: to consider or study an idea, a subject, etc. very carefully

data.chText: 这些观点将在第10章作更为详细的探讨。
data.enText: These ideas will be examined in more detail in Chapter 10.

data.chText: 有必要调查一下怎样才能实施这些方案。
data.enText: It is necessary to examine how the proposals can be carried out.

data.chText: （仔细地）检查，检验
data.enText: to look at sth/sb closely to see if there is anything wrong or to find the cause of a problem

data.chText: 货物到达时检查是否有破损。
data.enText: The goods were examined for damage on arrival.

data.chText: 医生给她作了检查，但没发现什么问题。
data.enText: The doctor examined her but could find nothing wrong.

data.chText: 考，测验（某人）
data.enText: to give sb a test to see how much they know about a subject or what they can do

data.chText: 期末时学生须参加所有学科的考试。
data.enText: The students will be examined in all subjects at the end of term.

data.chText: 只考你在本学期学的课程。
data.enText: You are only being examined on this semester's work.

data.chText: （尤指在法庭上）审问，查问
data.enText: to ask sb questions formally, especially in court
need (to have) your head examined

data.chText: 发疯
data.enText: to be crazy

data.text: check ♦ examine ♦ inspect ♦ go over sth

data.chText: 以上各词均含仔细检查、审查之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to look at sth/sb closely to make sure that everything is correct, in good condition, or acceptable.
check

data.chText: 指检查人或事物、审查、查核，以确保正确、正常和安全：
data.enText: to look at sb/sth closely to make sure that everything is correct, in good condition, safe or satisfactory

data.chText: 交作业前先检查一遍。
data.enText: Check your work before handing it in.
examine

data.chText: 指仔细检查人或事物、检验，以确认有无问题或找出问题所在：
data.enText: to look at sb/sth closely to see if there is anything wrong or to find the cause of a problem

data.chText: 货物到达时检查是否有破损。
data.enText: The goods were examined for damage on arrival.
inspect

data.chText: 指检查、查看、审视，以确保一切正常完好；视察（学校、工厂等）：
data.enText: to look at sb/sth closely to make sure that everything is satisfactory; to officially visit a school, factory, etc. in order to check that rules are being obeyed and that standards are acceptable

data.chText: 要确保在签收货物之前进行检验。
data.enText: Make sure you inspect the goods before signing for them.

data.chText: 旅游局至少每年视察一次所有举荐的旅馆。
data.enText: The Tourist Board inspects all recommended hotels at least once a year.

data.chText: 用check、examine还是inspect？
以上各词均可用于检查可能出现的问题，但检查错误只用check：
data.enText: All these words can be used when you are looking for possible problems, but only check is used for mistakes.
Examine/Inspect your work before handing it in.

data.chText: 查找问题的原因只用examine：
data.enText: Only examine is used when looking for the cause of a problem.
The doctor checked/inspected her but could find nothing wrong.

data.chText: examine较常用于专业人员所做的检查：
data.enText: Examine is used more often about a professional person.

data.chText: 房屋鉴定人检查了墙壁，看是否有水渍。
data.enText: The surveyor examined the walls for signs of damp.

data.chText: inspect较常用于官方检查：
data.enText: Inspect is used more often about an official.

data.chText: 公共卫生官员被召来视察了这家餐馆。
data.enText: Public health officials were called in to inspect the restaurant.
check, examine or inspect?
go over sth

data.chText: 指仔细检查看是否有错误、损坏或危险：
data.enText: to check sth carefully for mistakes, damage or anything dangerous

data.chText: 交作业前仔细检查一下拼写错误。
data.enText: Go over your work for spelling mistakes before you hand it in.
to check/examine/inspect/go over (sth) for sth
to check/examine/inspect/go over sth to see if/whether…
to check/examine/inspect/go over sth carefully/thoroughly

data.text: examine ♦ review ♦ study ♦ take stock ♦ survey

data.chText: 以上各词均含思量、审查、调查、研究之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to think about, study or describe sb/sth carefully, especially in order to understand them, form an opinion of them or make a decision about them.
examine

data.chText: 指审查、调查、考查、考察：
data.enText: to think about, study or describe an idea, subject or piece of work very carefully

data.chText: 这些观点将在第10章作更为详细的探讨。
data.enText: These ideas will be examined in more detail in Chapter 10.
review

data.chText: 指复查、检讨，以进行必要的修改：
data.enText: to examine sth again, especially so that you can decide if it is necessary to make changes

data.chText: 政府将在今年晚些时候重新检讨形势。
data.enText: The government will review the situation later in the year.
study

data.chText: 指研究、调查：
data.enText: to examine sb/sth in order to understand them or it

data.chText: 我们将认真研究这份报告，然后再作决定。
data.enText: We will study the report carefully before making a decision.

data.chText: 用examine还是study？
为理解或帮助别人理解某事，如在书中探讨，用examine；为使自己理解某事，用study。
data.enText: You examine sth in order to understand it or to help other people understand it, for example by describing it in a book; you study sth in order to understand it yourself.
examine or study?
take stock (of sth)

data.chText: 指对情况加以总结、作出评估、进行反思：
data.enText: to think carefully about the way in which a particular situation is developing in order to decide what to do next

data.chText: 他该从旁观者的角度来反思一下自己的职业生涯了。
data.enText: It was time to stand back and take stock of his career.
survey

data.chText: 指总体研究、全面评述、概述：
data.enText: to examine and give a general description of sth

data.chText: 本章对欧洲政治的现状作了简略概述。
data.enText: This chapter briefly surveys the current state of European politics.
to examine/review/study/take stock of/survey what/how/whether…
to examine/review/study/take stock of/survey the situation
to examine/review/study/survey the evidence
to examine/review/study/take stock of/survey sth briefly/regularly
to examine/review/study sth carefully/systematically/thoroughly/fully/further
to examine/review/study sth closely/in depth/in detail

ex.chText: 一个由政府官员组成的小组正在调查此事件。
ex.enText: A group of government officials are investigating the incident.

ex.chText: 他因涉嫌挪用公款而正在接受警方调查。
ex.enText: He is being investigated by the police on suspicion of embezzlement.

synonyms.bx: 指查明事故、犯罪、科学问题等的真相。

ex.chText: 警察得检查这唯一的物证有没有指纹。
ex.enText: The police will have to examine the only piece of physical evidence for fingerprints.

ex.chText: 一队专家被派去检查飞机的残骸。
ex.enText: A team of experts were sent to examine the wreckage of the airplane.

synonyms.bx: 表示仔细、彻底地查看某物，以便发现更多信息。

ex.chText: 他们勘查那座山以北的地区了吗？
ex.enText: Did they explore the land to the north of the mountain?

ex.chText: 巴黎是个值得考察的美妙城市。
ex.enText: Paris is a wonderful city to explore.

synonyms.bx: 指走访并探察某地以了解相关信息。

ex.chText: 她总是想过多地打探别人的私事。
ex.enText: She always wants to probe too deeply into others' personal affairs.

ex.chText: 警方已经就有人称他出售假药一事进行了调查。
ex.enText: The police have probed claims that he sold fake medicine.

synonyms.bx: 指追查不为人知的事，尤指打探别人不愿透露的事。

data.enText: need (to have) your head examined

data.chText: 发疯
data.enText: to be crazy

tr: consider in detail and subject to an analysis in order to discover essential features or meaning
example: analyze the evidence in a criminal trial

tr: question or examine thoroughly and closely
observe, check out, and look over carefully or inspect
example: The customs agent examined the baggage
I must see your passport before you can enter the country

tr: put to the test, as for its quality, or give experimental use to
example: This approach has been tried with good results

value.def: If you examine something, you look at it carefully.

example.ex: He examined her passport and stamped it...
example.tran: 他仔细检查了她的护照，然后在上面盖了章。

example.ex: Forensic scientists are examining what police believe to have been the bombers' car.
example.tran: 法医学家正在对一辆警方怀疑属于投弹者的汽车进行仔细检查。

example.ex: The Navy is to carry out an examination of the wreck tomorrow...
example.tran: 海军明天将对失事船只进行细查。

example.ex: They have also searched offices in Sheffield and taken away documents for examination.
example.tran: 他们还搜查了位于设菲尔德的办公室，并带走了一些文件进行仔细检查。

value.def: If a doctor examines you, he or she looks at your body, feels it, or does simple tests in order to check how healthy you are.

example.ex: Another doctor examined her and could still find nothing wrong...
example.tran: 另外一名医生对她进行了诊察，仍旧没有发现任何问题。

example.ex: He was examined again and then prescribed a different herbal medicine.
example.tran: 医生又对他诊察了一遍，然后开了另外一种草药。

example.ex: He was later discharged after an examination at Westminster Hospital...
example.tran: 在威斯敏斯特医院进行了一次诊察后他就出院了。

example.ex: Further examination is needed to exclude the chance of disease.
example.tran: 需要进一步检查以排除患病的可能。

value.def: If an idea, proposal, or plan is examined, it is considered very carefully.

example.ex: I have given the matter much thought, examining all the possible alternatives...
example.tran: 这个问题我已经考虑了很多，分析了各种可能的选择。

example.ex: The plans will be examined by EU environment ministers.
example.tran: 欧盟各国环境部部长将仔细研究这些计划。

example.ex: The proposal requires careful examination and consideration.
example.tran: 那项提议需要经过仔细研究和考虑。

value.def: If you are examined, you are given a formal test in order to show your knowledge of a subject.

example.ex: ...learning to cope with the pressures of being judged and examined by our teachers.
example.tran: 学会应对老师评判和测验时的压力

trans: 审核；当当网在经过审核；核查
